# 🔹 Closure (Kleene Star)

Given:

```text
Σ={a,b}
```

Then

[
Σ^*
]

means:

**All possible finite strings** over Σ.

Example:

```text
ε
a
b
aa
ab
ba
bb
aaa
...
```

Infinite.

---

# 🔹 Positive Closure

Notation:

[
Σ^+
]

Contains:

All strings except ε.

Relationship:

[
Σ^+=Σ^*-{\varepsilon}
]

