# 🔹 Finite Automaton (FA)

A **Finite Automaton** is the simplest computational model.

It consists of:

[
(Q,\Sigma,\delta,q_0,F)
]

Where:

| Symbol | Meaning                  |
| ------ | ------------------------ |
| Q      | Set of states            |
| Σ      | Input alphabet           |
| δ      | Transition function      |
| q₀     | Start state              |
| F      | Final (accepting) states |

📌 This 5-tuple definition is **one of the most frequently asked GATE questions**.

---

# 🔹 Example of a Finite Automaton

Language:

All binary strings ending with **1**.

States:

```text
q0 → Start

q1 → Accept
```

Transition Table:

| Current State | Input 0 | Input 1 |
| ------------- | ------- | ------- |
| q0            | q0      | q1      |
| q1            | q0      | q1      |

Accepting State:

```text
q1
```

---

# 🔹 Applications of Finite Automata

* Lexical Analysis (Compiler Design)
* Pattern Matching
* Text Editors
* Network Protocols
* Spell Checkers
* Digital Circuit Design

